Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression, the rear shows impressions of textile, perpendicular to it two lines of a turned string. The fine brown Nile clay has few inclusions of mica and was hardened after excavation. The top part is rounded at the edges and covered with finger impressions, there is part of a scarab-like seal impression. The seal shows very small clear cut signs, probably mn-nfr, some signs broken off, underneath wsr H-... maybe nw-vessel (W24), rest broken off.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
